[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Shrinking head</b></col> <fld>(Founding)</fld>, <cd>a
body of molten metal connected with a mold for the purpose of supplying
metal to compensate for the shrinkage of the casting; -- called also
<altname>sinking head</altname>, and
<altname>riser</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shrinkingly</ent>⟦br⟧
